
// Very capable sketch for automation of a chicken coop.
// It does require a wifi signal for the sunrise and sunset times including DST.
// fill in your wifi and lat and long credentials in the secrets. h tab
// It turns the coop light on before sunset and turns off after the door closes. Easily adjusted in "USER SETTINGS" (close to the top of the  sketch)
// The door opens in the morning after sunrise and closes with a safety, close-open-close to release any chickens that might be in the door way.
// The code has safety time outs to prevent motor burnout if there is a promblem and also door open and close timeouts to keep things sweet.
// There is simple Fault diagnois in the stored events page with time stamps for each.
// Everything is controlled by the rotary encoder, in the manual page turn CW or CCW for manual door opening and closing and  manual light on/off .
// The encoders push button has 3 functions, short press wake and change display pages. 3 second press to manually turn the light on/off and long press 5 seconds for resetting faults.
// The system does a automatic reset each day at midnight.
// There a fault buzzer and flashing red fault light if something is wrong.
// This system uses a ESP32 S3 N16R8 with external antenner. 1.3" OLED i2C display, DS3231 RTC, KY-040 rotary controller and a modular 3.3v relay board for the light.
// The door is a vertical drop door using a motor and pulley and a bit of string.
// Door motor is a 12 volt JGB37-520 geared to 22RPM, slower might be better, L298N motor controller and two"NO"reed limit switches that oporate with magnets, these tell the system if the door is open of closed.
// The whole System is powered by a 12v 100w / 8 amp power supply and a DC to DC buck to reduce the voltage down to 5v for the ESP32 board.
// All connections in the GPIO block close to the top of the sketch
// All of the electronics purchased from AliExpress and a fraction of the cost of Amazon.

